</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="631" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="12.[149,1353,2247,3459]" lastBlockId="12.[1426,2628,283,514]" pageId="12" pageNumber="631">
<emphasis box="[151,497,3387,3420]" pageId="12" pageNumber="631">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Least Concern in The 
<collectionCode box="[984,1063,3387,3420]" pageId="12" pageNumber="631">IUCN</collectionCode>
Red List. The subspecies M. m. tsuensisis classified as Vulnerable. The Japanese Marten is trapped forits fur during the hunting season (1 December to 31 January), except on 
<collectingRegion box="[2385,2523,283,316]" country="Japan" name="Hokkaido" pageId="12" pageNumber="631">Hokkaido</collectingRegion>
Island. The subspecies M. m. tsuensis, found only on the Tsushima Islands, has been protected from trapping since 1971. Predation by feral dogs and highway mortality appear to be major threats.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
